ReviewText: I recently came across this coffee and am so glad I did. As a child, I used to spend 2p of my 7p weekly pocket money on a sachet of Nescafe original. My parents were tea drinkers but I was born a coffee lover. Nescafe Gold barista style is a truly authentic barista tasting coffee, a party on the taste buds! It has all the taste of fresh ground but none of the mess or hassle of cleaning out cafetieres or machines. The advantage too is stays hotter as no machine involved. Truly lovely, smooth, full-flavoured robust coffee, with the exceptional quality one has come to expect from Nescafe! Excellent.
Title: Barista style taste without the fuss in an instant

ReviewText: Nescafe Gold Blend Barista Style Coffee is perfect for Coffee lovers that love the deep rich flavour of the roast , while it may appear to be more expensive than other coffees the Flavour more than makes up for the price , after all if you walked into a Coffee shop you'd be paying more for 2 cups than for an entire Carton . I have 2 ways of drinking this , either black and very strong or it makes a fantastic Latte just heat some milk in the microwave with a sprinkling of cinnamon then add 2 heaped teaspoons of coffee and top up with Hot water , it creates a delicious milky foam and keeps you coming back for more !
Title: Barista style Coffee at Home

ReviewText: From the moment I poured in the water on top of my heaped tea spoon of Nescafe Gold Barista style coffee it was pure bliss from the smell of the coffee invoking memoires of me in London a student ordering my first expresso from a very large Italian gentleman who told me “maybe you try a latte” but I thought been a woman of the world I’d be well able for it.  He was right I couldn’t even try a second sip.  Been the nice Italian man that he was he fired up his machine and produced a froughty milky mug and popped my expresso into it.  It was lovely I enjoyed it so much.  That was nearly 30 years ago but the smell and taste of the barista style coffee is timeless.
Title: Hidden Memeries

ReviewText: I bought this after my usual instant was sold out and I now have a new favourite! It's gorgeous flavour & smell brings the coffee shop to your kitchen. For me, anytime of day is a good time for coffee and I can already see this will last longer than my regular coffee brand
Title: Barista Style it most definitely is!

ReviewText:

It's good coffee, I do like my coffee strong (like 3 tea spoons) so I was converned this would have a weaker flavour but it doesn't, it's nice, smooth ... has a bit of a smokey kind of flavour to it.  Im not sure what makes it "Barista Style" but it's a tasty coffee ... the wee tin is handy for keeping pennies in too when you're done :)

ReviewText: I have purchased this coffee on two occasions now. I enjoy a good strong cup of coffee and have not been disappointed with this one. I am a bit fussy about my coffee, but this one definitely satisfies my needs. It is smooth, full bodied and definitely not bitter, my second favourite Nescafe product.

ReviewText: First time I tried this was at a friends house so I didn't know what I was drinking at first. I asked if they had got a new coffee machine and they whipped out a tin of this stuff. SOLD! I bought a tin on my way home and now it always tops the shopping list. Nescafe Gold blend barista style has a rich, full flavour that I didn't think was possible to get from an instant coffee. Now I can have the barista experience at home in my pyjamas (as opposed to out in some expensive barista cafe in my pyjamas...) I've also since been reading some interesting articles on the Nescafe Plan which is a global initiative to support coffee farmers and develop more sustainable coffee farming so it's good to know that sales from Nescafe's range are supporting good causes.
